{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"OK. We've heard a lot of people"},{"time":3000,"text":"speak at this conference"},{"time":5000,"text":"about the power of the human mind."},{"time":8000,"text":"And what I'd like to do today"},{"time":10000,"text":"is give you a vivid example"},{"time":12000,"text":"of how that power can be unleashed"},{"time":14000,"text":"when someone is in a survival situation,"},{"time":17000,"text":"how the will to survive can bring that out in people."},{"time":21000,"text":"This is an incident which occurred on Mount Everest;"},{"time":24000,"text":"it was the worst disaster in the history of Everest."},{"time":28000,"text":"And when it occurred, I was the only doctor on the mountain."},{"time":31000,"text":"So I'll take you through that"},{"time":33000,"text":"and we'll see what it's like"},{"time":36000,"text":"when someone really"},{"time":38000,"text":"summons the will to survive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"OK, this is Mount Everest."},{"time":42000,"text":"It's 29,035 feet high."},{"time":44000,"text":"I've been there six times: Four times I did work with National Geographic,"},{"time":47000,"text":"making tectonic plate measurements;"},{"time":49000,"text":"twice, I went with NASA"},{"time":51000,"text":"doing remote sensing devices."},{"time":54000,"text":"It was on my fourth trip to Everest"},{"time":56000,"text":"that a comet passed over the mountain. Hyakutake."},{"time":59000,"text":"And the Sherpas told us then"},{"time":61000,"text":"that was a very bad omen,"},{"time":63000,"text":"and we should have listened to them."},{"time":65000,"text":"Everest is an extreme environment."},{"time":68000,"text":"There's only one-third as much oxygen at the summit as there is at sea level."},{"time":71000,"text":"Near the summit, temperatures"},{"time":73000,"text":"can be 40 degrees below zero."},{"time":75000,"text":"You can have winds 20 to 40 miles an hour."},{"time":77000,"text":"It's actually a wind-chill factor"},{"time":79000,"text":"which is lower than a summer day on Mars."},{"time":83000,"text":"I remember one time being up near the summit,"},{"time":85000,"text":"I reached into my down jacket"},{"time":87000,"text":"for a drink from my water bottle,"},{"time":89000,"text":"inside my down jacket,"},{"time":91000,"text":"only to discover that the water was already frozen solid."},{"time":94000,"text":"That gives you an idea of just how severe"},{"time":96000,"text":"things are near the summit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"OK, this is the route up Everest."},{"time":102000,"text":"It starts at base camp, at 17,500 feet."},{"time":106000,"text":"Camp One, 2,000 feet higher."},{"time":109000,"text":"Camp Two, another 2,000 feet higher up,"},{"time":111000,"text":"what's called the Western Cwm."},{"time":113000,"text":"CampThree is at the base of Lhotse,"},{"time":115000,"text":"which is the fourth highest mountain in the world, but it's dwarfed by Everest."},{"time":118000,"text":"And then Camp Four is the highest camp;"},{"time":121000,"text":"that's 3,000 feet short of the summit."},{"time":125000,"text":"This is a view of base camp."},{"time":127000,"text":"This is pitched on a glacier at 17,500 feet."},{"time":130000,"text":"It's the highest point you can bring your yaks"},{"time":132000,"text":"before you have to unload."},{"time":134000,"text":"And this is what they unloaded for me:"},{"time":136000,"text":"I had four yak loads of medical supplies,"},{"time":138000,"text":"which are dumped in a tent,"},{"time":140000,"text":"and here I am trying to arrange things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"This was our expedition."},{"time":145000,"text":"It was a National Geographic expedition,"},{"time":147000,"text":"but it was organized by The Explorers Club."},{"time":149000,"text":"There were three other expeditions on the mountain,"},{"time":151000,"text":"an American team, a New Zealand team"},{"time":153000,"text":"and an IMAX team."},{"time":157000,"text":"And, after actually two months of preparation,"},{"time":160000,"text":"we built our camps all the way up the mountain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"This is a view looking up the icefall,"},{"time":165000,"text":"the first 2,000 feet of the climb"},{"time":167000,"text":"up from base camp."},{"time":170000,"text":"And here's a picture in the icefall;"},{"time":172000,"text":"it's a waterfall, but it's frozen, but it moves very slowly,"},{"time":175000,"text":"and it actually changes every day."},{"time":177000,"text":"When you're in it, you're like a rat in a maze;"},{"time":179000,"text":"you can't even see over the top."},{"time":182000,"text":"This is near the top of the icefall."},{"time":184000,"text":"You want to climb through at night when the ice is frozen."},{"time":187000,"text":"That way, it's less likely to tumble down on you."},{"time":189000,"text":"These are some climbers reaching the top of the icefall just at sun-up."},{"time":195000,"text":"This is me crossing a crevasse."},{"time":197000,"text":"We cross on aluminum ladders with safety ropes attached."},{"time":202000,"text":"That's another crevasse."},{"time":204000,"text":"Some of these things are 10 stories deep or more,"},{"time":206000,"text":"and one of my climbing friends says that"},{"time":208000,"text":"the reason we actually climb at night"},{"time":210000,"text":"is because if we ever saw the bottom"},{"time":212000,"text":"of what we're climbing over,"},{"time":214000,"text":"we would never do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"Okay. This is Camp One."},{"time":219000,"text":"It's the first flat spot you can reach"},{"time":221000,"text":"after you get up to the top of the icefall."},{"time":224000,"text":"And from there we climb up to Camp Two,"},{"time":227000,"text":"which is sort of the foreground."},{"time":229000,"text":"These are climbers moving up the Lhotse face,"},{"time":231000,"text":"that mountain toward Camp Three."},{"time":233000,"text":"They're on fixed ropes here."},{"time":235000,"text":"A fall here, if you weren't roped in,"},{"time":237000,"text":"would be 5,000 feet down."},{"time":241000,"text":"This is a view taken from camp three."},{"time":243000,"text":"You can see the Lhotse face is in profile,"},{"time":245000,"text":"it's about a 45 degree angle. It takes two days to climb it,"},{"time":248000,"text":"so you put the camp halfway through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"If you notice, the summit of Everest is black."},{"time":252000,"text":"There's no ice over it."},{"time":254000,"text":"And that's because Everest is so high,"},{"time":256000,"text":"it's in the jet stream,"},{"time":258000,"text":"and winds are constantly scouring the face,"},{"time":260000,"text":"so no snow gets to accumulate."},{"time":262000,"text":"What looks like a cloud behind the summit ridge"},{"time":264000,"text":"is actually snow being blown off the summit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270000,"text":"This is on the way up from Camp Three to Camp Four,"},{"time":272000,"text":"moving in, up through the clouds."},{"time":277000,"text":"And this is at Camp Four."},{"time":279000,"text":"Once you get to Camp Four, you have maybe 24 hours"},{"time":282000,"text":"to decide if you're going to go for the summit or not."},{"time":284000,"text":"Everybody's on oxygen, your supplies are limited,"},{"time":287000,"text":"and you either have to go up or go down,"},{"time":289000,"text":"make that decision very quickly."},{"time":292000,"text":"This is a picture of Rob Hall."},{"time":294000,"text":"He was the leader of the New Zealand team."},{"time":296000,"text":"This is a radio he used later to call his wife"},{"time":298000,"text":"that I'll tell you about."},{"time":302000,"text":"These are some climbers waiting to go to the summit."},{"time":304000,"text":"They're up at Camp Four, and you can see that there's wind blowing off the summit."},{"time":307000,"text":"This is not good weather to climb in,"},{"time":309000,"text":"so the climbers are just waiting, hoping that the wind's going to die down."},{"time":314000,"text":"And, in fact, the wind does die down at night."},{"time":316000,"text":"It becomes very calm, there's no wind at all."},{"time":318000,"text":"This looks like a good chance to go for the summit."},{"time":321000,"text":"So here are some climbers starting out for the summit"},{"time":323000,"text":"on what's called the Triangular Face."},{"time":325000,"text":"It's the first part of climb."},{"time":327000,"text":"It's done in the dark, because it's actually less steep than what comes next,"},{"time":329000,"text":"and you can gain daylight hours if you do this in the dark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333000,"text":"So that's what happened."},{"time":335000,"text":"The climbers got on the southeast ridge."},{"time":337000,"text":"This is the view looking at the southeast ridge."},{"time":339000,"text":"The summit would be in the foreground."},{"time":341000,"text":"From here, it's about 1,500 feet"},{"time":344000,"text":"up at a 30-degree angle to the summit."},{"time":349000,"text":"But what happened that year was"},{"time":351000,"text":"the wind suddenly and unexpectedly picked up."},{"time":353000,"text":"A storm blew in that no one was anticipating."},{"time":356000,"text":"You can see here some ferocious winds"},{"time":358000,"text":"blowing snow way high off the summit."},{"time":361000,"text":"And there were climbers on that summit ridge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"This is a picture of me in that area"},{"time":367000,"text":"taken a year before,"},{"time":369000,"text":"and you can see I've got an oxygen mask on"},{"time":372000,"text":"with a rebreather."},{"time":374000,"text":"I have an oxygen hose connected here."},{"time":376000,"text":"You can see on this climber, we have two oxygen tanks in the backpack --"},{"time":379000,"text":"little titanium tanks, very lightweight --"},{"time":381000,"text":"and we're not carrying much else."},{"time":383000,"text":"This is all you've got. You're very exposed on the summit ridge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"OK, this is a view taken on the summit ridge itself."},{"time":389000,"text":"This is on the way toward the summit,"},{"time":391000,"text":"on that 1,500-foot bridge."},{"time":394000,"text":"All the climbers here are climbing unroped,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and the reason is because"},{"time":398000,"text":"the drop off is so sheer on either side"},{"time":400000,"text":"that if you were roped to somebody,"},{"time":402000,"text":"you'd wind up just pulling them off with you."},{"time":404000,"text":"So each person climbs individually."},{"time":406000,"text":"And it's not a straight path at all,"},{"time":409000,"text":"it's very difficult climbing,"},{"time":412000,"text":"and there's always the risk"},{"time":414000,"text":"of falling on either side."},{"time":416000,"text":"If you fall to your left, you're going to fall"},{"time":418000,"text":"8,000 feet into Nepal;"},{"time":420000,"text":"if you fall to your right,"},{"time":422000,"text":"you're going to fall 12,000 feet into Tibet."},{"time":425000,"text":"So it's probably better to fall into Tibet"},{"time":427000,"text":"because you'll live longer."},{"time":429000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":434000,"text":"But, either way, you fall for the rest of your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"OK. Those climbers were up near the summit,"},{"time":440000,"text":"along that summit ridge that you see up there,"},{"time":444000,"text":"and I was down here in Camp Three."},{"time":446000,"text":"My expedition was down in Camp Three,"},{"time":449000,"text":"while these guys were up there in the storm."},{"time":451000,"text":"The storm was so fierce that we had to lay,"},{"time":454000,"text":"fully dressed, fully equipped,"},{"time":456000,"text":"laid out on the tent floor"},{"time":458000,"text":"to stop the tent from blowing off the mountain."},{"time":460000,"text":"It was the worst winds I've ever seen."},{"time":462000,"text":"And the climbers up on the ridge"},{"time":465000,"text":"were that much higher, 2,000 feet higher,"},{"time":467000,"text":"and completely exposed to the elements."},{"time":471000,"text":"We were in radio contact with some of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"This is a view taken along the summit ridge."},{"time":476000,"text":"Rob Hall, we heard by radio,"},{"time":478000,"text":"was up here, at this point in the storm"},{"time":481000,"text":"with Doug Hansen."},{"time":483000,"text":"And we heard that Rob was OK,"},{"time":485000,"text":"but Doug was too weak to come down."},{"time":487000,"text":"He was exhausted, and Rob was staying with him."},{"time":491000,"text":"We also got some bad news in the storm"},{"time":493000,"text":"that Beck Weathers, another climber,"},{"time":496000,"text":"had collapsed in the snow and was dead."},{"time":499000,"text":"There were still 18 other climbers"},{"time":501000,"text":"that we weren't aware of their condition."},{"time":505000,"text":"They were lost. There was total confusion on the mountain;"},{"time":509000,"text":"all the stories were confusing, most of them were conflicting."},{"time":512000,"text":"We really had no idea what was going on during that storm."},{"time":515000,"text":"We were just hunkered down"},{"time":517000,"text":"in our tents at Camp Three."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Our two strongest climbers, Todd Burleson and Pete Athans,"},{"time":522000,"text":"decided to go up to try to rescue who they could"},{"time":525000,"text":"even though there was a ferocious storm going."},{"time":528000,"text":"They tried to radio a message to Rob Hall,"},{"time":531000,"text":"who was a superb climber"},{"time":534000,"text":"stuck, sort of, with a weak climber"},{"time":536000,"text":"up near the summit."},{"time":538000,"text":"I expected them to say to Rob,"},{"time":540000,"text":"\"Hold on. We're coming.\""},{"time":543000,"text":"But in fact, what they said was,"},{"time":546000,"text":"\"Leave Doug and come down yourself."},{"time":548000,"text":"There's no chance of saving him,"},{"time":550000,"text":"and just try to save yourself at this point.\""},{"time":554000,"text":"And Rob got that message,"},{"time":556000,"text":"but his answer was,"},{"time":559000,"text":"\"We're both listening.\""},{"time":565000,"text":"Todd and Pete got up to the summit ridge, up in here,"},{"time":568000,"text":"and it was a scene of complete chaos up there."},{"time":572000,"text":"But they did what they could to stabilize the people."},{"time":575000,"text":"I gave them radio advice from Camp Three,"},{"time":578000,"text":"and we sent down the climbers that could make it down"},{"time":581000,"text":"under their own power."},{"time":583000,"text":"The ones that couldn't we just sort of decided to leave up at Camp Four."},{"time":586000,"text":"So the climbers were coming down along this route."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"This is taken from Camp Three, where I was."},{"time":591000,"text":"And they all came by me"},{"time":593000,"text":"so I could take a look at them and see what I could do for them,"},{"time":597000,"text":"which is really not much, because Camp Three"},{"time":599000,"text":"is a little notch cut in the ice"},{"time":601000,"text":"in the middle of a 45-degree angle."},{"time":603000,"text":"You can barely stand outside the tent."},{"time":605000,"text":"It's really cold; it's 24,000 feet."},{"time":607000,"text":"The only supplies I had at that altitude"},{"time":609000,"text":"were two plastic bags"},{"time":611000,"text":"with preloaded syringes"},{"time":613000,"text":"of painkiller and steroids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"So, as the climbers came by me,"},{"time":618000,"text":"I sort of assessed whether or not they were in condition"},{"time":620000,"text":"to continue on further down."},{"time":622000,"text":"The ones that weren't that lucid or were not that well coordinated,"},{"time":625000,"text":"I would give an injection of steroids"},{"time":628000,"text":"to try to give them some period"},{"time":630000,"text":"of lucidity and coordination"},{"time":632000,"text":"where they could then work their way further down the mountain."},{"time":635000,"text":"It's so awkward to work up there that sometimes"},{"time":637000,"text":"I even gave the injections right through their clothes."},{"time":639000,"text":"It was just too hard to maneuver"},{"time":642000,"text":"any other way up there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"While I was taking care of them,"},{"time":646000,"text":"we got more news about Rob Hall."},{"time":648000,"text":"There was no way we could get up high enough to rescue him."},{"time":652000,"text":"He called in to say that he was alone now."},{"time":655000,"text":"Apparently, Doug had died higher up on the mountain."},{"time":658000,"text":"But Rob was now too weak to come down himself,"},{"time":661000,"text":"and with the fierce winds and up at that altitude,"},{"time":664000,"text":"he was just beyond rescue"},{"time":666000,"text":"and he knew it."},{"time":668000,"text":"At that point, he asked"},{"time":670000,"text":"to be paged into his wife."},{"time":672000,"text":"He was carrying a radio."},{"time":674000,"text":"His wife was home in New Zealand,"},{"time":676000,"text":"seven months pregnant with their first child,"},{"time":679000,"text":"and Rob asked to be patched into her. That was done,"},{"time":682000,"text":"and Rob and his wife"},{"time":684000,"text":"had their last conversation."},{"time":686000,"text":"They picked the name for their baby."},{"time":688000,"text":"Rob then signed off,"},{"time":690000,"text":"and that was the last we ever heard of him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"I was faced with treating a lot of critically ill patients"},{"time":698000,"text":"at 24,000 feet,"},{"time":700000,"text":"which was an impossibility."},{"time":702000,"text":"So what we did was, we got the victims"},{"time":704000,"text":"down to 21,000 feet, where it was easier for me to treat them."},{"time":707000,"text":"This was my medical kit."},{"time":709000,"text":"It's a tackle box filled with medical supplies."},{"time":712000,"text":"This is what I carried up the mountain."},{"time":715000,"text":"I had more supplies lower down,"},{"time":717000,"text":"which I asked to be brought up to meet me at the lower camp."},{"time":720000,"text":"And this was scene at the lower camp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722000,"text":"The survivors came in one by one."},{"time":725000,"text":"Some of them were hypothermic,"},{"time":727000,"text":"some of them were frostbitten, some were both."},{"time":730000,"text":"What we did was try to warm them up as best we could,"},{"time":733000,"text":"put oxygen on them and try to revive them,"},{"time":736000,"text":"which is difficult to do at 21,000 feet,"},{"time":739000,"text":"when the tent is freezing."},{"time":743000,"text":"This is some severe frostbite on the feet,"},{"time":746000,"text":"severe frostbite on the nose."},{"time":752000,"text":"This climber was snow blind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"As I was taking care of these climbers,"},{"time":756000,"text":"we got a startling experience."},{"time":761000,"text":"Out of nowhere, Beck Weathers,"},{"time":763000,"text":"who we had already been told was dead,"},{"time":766000,"text":"stumbled into the tent,"},{"time":769000,"text":"just like a mummy, he walked into the tent."},{"time":772000,"text":"I expected him to be incoherent,"},{"time":774000,"text":"but, in fact, he walked into the tent and said to me,"},{"time":776000,"text":"\"Hi, Ken. Where should I sit?\""},{"time":779000,"text":"And then he said,"},{"time":781000,"text":"\"Do you accept my health insurance?\""},{"time":783000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":785000,"text":"He really said that."},{"time":787000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":789000,"text":"So he was completely lucid, but he was very severely frostbitten."},{"time":792000,"text":"You can see his hand is completely white;"},{"time":794000,"text":"his face, his nose, is burned."},{"time":796000,"text":"First, it turns white, and then when it's completed necrosis,"},{"time":799000,"text":"it turns black, and then it falls off."},{"time":802000,"text":"It's the last stage, just like a scar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"So, as I was taking care of Beck,"},{"time":806000,"text":"he related what had been going on up there."},{"time":808000,"text":"He said he had gotten lost in the storm,"},{"time":811000,"text":"collapsed in the snow,"},{"time":813000,"text":"and just laid there, unable to move."},{"time":815000,"text":"Some climbers had come by and looked at him,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and he heard them say, \"He's dead.\""},{"time":822000,"text":"But Beck wasn't dead; he heard that,"},{"time":825000,"text":"but he was completely unable to move."},{"time":827000,"text":"He was in some sort of catatonic state"},{"time":829000,"text":"where he could be aware of his surroundings,"},{"time":831000,"text":"but couldn't even blink to indicate that he was alive."},{"time":834000,"text":"So the climbers passed him by,"},{"time":837000,"text":"and Beck lay there for a day, a night"},{"time":840000,"text":"and another day,"},{"time":842000,"text":"in the snow."},{"time":844000,"text":"And then he said to himself,"},{"time":846000,"text":"\"I don't want to die."},{"time":848000,"text":"I have a family to come back to.\""},{"time":850000,"text":"And the thoughts of his family,"},{"time":852000,"text":"his kids and his wife,"},{"time":854000,"text":"generated enough energy,"},{"time":857000,"text":"enough motivation in him,"},{"time":859000,"text":"so that he actually got up."},{"time":861000,"text":"After laying in the snow that long a time,"},{"time":863000,"text":"he got up and found his way back to the camp."},{"time":867000,"text":"And Beck told me that story very quietly,"},{"time":869000,"text":"but I was absolutely stunned by it."},{"time":872000,"text":"I couldn't imagine anybody laying in the snow"},{"time":874000,"text":"that long a time"},{"time":876000,"text":"and then getting up."},{"time":878000,"text":"He apparently reversed"},{"time":880000,"text":"an irreversible hypothermia."},{"time":883000,"text":"And I can only try to speculate"},{"time":886000,"text":"on how he did it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"So, what if we had Beck"},{"time":890000,"text":"hooked up to a SPECT scan,"},{"time":892000,"text":"something that could actually measure brain function?"},{"time":897000,"text":"Just very simply, the three parts of the brain:"},{"time":900000,"text":"the frontal lobe, where you focus"},{"time":902000,"text":"your attention and concentration;"},{"time":904000,"text":"you have the temporal lobe,"},{"time":906000,"text":"where you form images and keep memories;"},{"time":908000,"text":"and the posterior part of your brain,"},{"time":910000,"text":"which contains the cerebellum, which controls motion;"},{"time":912000,"text":"and the brain stem,"},{"time":914000,"text":"where you have your basic maintenance functions,"},{"time":916000,"text":"like heartbeat and respiration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"So let's take a cut through the brain here,"},{"time":921000,"text":"and imagine that Beck"},{"time":923000,"text":"was hooked up to a SPECT scan."},{"time":925000,"text":"This measures dynamic blood flow"},{"time":927000,"text":"and therefore energy flow within the brain."},{"time":929000,"text":"So you have the prefrontal cortex here,"},{"time":931000,"text":"lighting up in red."},{"time":933000,"text":"This is a pretty evenly distributed scan."},{"time":935000,"text":"You have the middle area,"},{"time":937000,"text":"where the temporal lobe might be, in here,"},{"time":939000,"text":"and the posterior portion, where the maintenance functions are in the back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"This is a roughly normal scan,"},{"time":944000,"text":"showing equal distribution of energy."},{"time":948000,"text":"Now, you go to this one and you see how much more"},{"time":951000,"text":"the frontal lobes are lighting up."},{"time":953000,"text":"This might be what Beck would be experiencing"},{"time":955000,"text":"when he realizes he's in danger."},{"time":957000,"text":"He's focusing all his attention"},{"time":959000,"text":"on getting himself out of trouble."},{"time":961000,"text":"These parts of the brain are quieting down."},{"time":964000,"text":"He's not thinking about his family or anybody else at this point,"},{"time":967000,"text":"and he's working pretty hard."},{"time":969000,"text":"He's trying to get his muscles going and get out of this."},{"time":975000,"text":"OK, but he's losing ground here."},{"time":978000,"text":"He's running out of energy."},{"time":980000,"text":"It's too cold; he can't keep his metabolic fires going,"},{"time":983000,"text":"and, you see, there's no more red here;"},{"time":985000,"text":"his brain is quieting down."},{"time":987000,"text":"He's collapsed in the snow here. Everything is quiet,"},{"time":989000,"text":"there's very little red anywhere."},{"time":992000,"text":"Beck is powering down."},{"time":994000,"text":"He's dying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998000,"text":"You go on to the next scan,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"but, in Beck's case,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"you can see that the middle part of his brain"},{"time":1004000,"text":"is beginning to light up again."},{"time":1007000,"text":"He's beginning to think about his family."},{"time":1009000,"text":"He's beginning to have images"},{"time":1011000,"text":"that are motivating him to get up."},{"time":1013000,"text":"He's developing energy in this area"},{"time":1015000,"text":"through thought."},{"time":1017000,"text":"And this is how he's going to turn thought"},{"time":1020000,"text":"back into action."},{"time":1023000,"text":"This part of the brain is called the anterior cingulate gyrus."},{"time":1025000,"text":"It's an area in which"},{"time":1027000,"text":"a lot of neuroscientists believe"},{"time":1030000,"text":"the seat of will exists."},{"time":1032000,"text":"This is where people make decisions, where they develop willpower."},{"time":1035000,"text":"And, you can see, there's an energy flow"},{"time":1037000,"text":"going from the mid portion of his brain,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"where he's got images of his family,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"into this area, which is powering his will."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046000,"text":"Okay. This is getting stronger and stronger"},{"time":1048000,"text":"to the point where it's actually"},{"time":1050000,"text":"going to be a motivating factor."},{"time":1052000,"text":"He's going to develop enough energy in that area --"},{"time":1054000,"text":"after a day, a night and a day --"},{"time":1056000,"text":"to actually motivate himself to get up."},{"time":1062000,"text":"And you can see here,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"he's starting to get more energy into the frontal lobe."},{"time":1066000,"text":"He's beginning to focus, he can concentrate now."},{"time":1069000,"text":"He's thinking about what he's got to do to save himself."},{"time":1071000,"text":"So this energy has been transmitted"},{"time":1073000,"text":"up toward the front of his brain,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"and it's getting quieter down here,"},{"time":1077000,"text":"but he's using this energy"},{"time":1079000,"text":"to think about what he has to do to get himself going."},{"time":1082000,"text":"And then, that energy is sort of spreading"},{"time":1085000,"text":"throughout his thought areas."},{"time":1087000,"text":"He's not thinking about his family now, and he's getting himself motivated."},{"time":1090000,"text":"This is the posterior part, where his muscles are going to be moving,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and he's going to be pacing himself."},{"time":1095000,"text":"His heart and lungs are going to pick up speed."},{"time":1098000,"text":"So this is what I can speculate might have been going on"},{"time":1101000,"text":"had we been able to do a SPECT scan on Beck"},{"time":1104000,"text":"during this survival epic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1108000,"text":"So here I am taking care of Beck at 21,000 feet,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"and I felt what I was doing was completely trivial"},{"time":1114000,"text":"compared to what he had done for himself."},{"time":1116000,"text":"It just shows you what the power of the mind can do."},{"time":1121000,"text":"He was critically ill, there were other critically ill patients;"},{"time":1123000,"text":"luckily, we were able to get a helicopter"},{"time":1125000,"text":"in to rescue these guys."},{"time":1128000,"text":"A helicopter came in at 21,000 feet"},{"time":1131000,"text":"and carried out the highest helicopter rescue in history."},{"time":1135000,"text":"It was able to land on the ice, take away Beck"},{"time":1137000,"text":"and the other survivors, one by one,"},{"time":1140000,"text":"and get them off to Kathmandu in a clinic"},{"time":1143000,"text":"before we even got back to base camp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146000,"text":"This is a scene at base camp,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"at one of the camps"},{"time":1150000,"text":"where some of the climbers were lost."},{"time":1152000,"text":"And we had a memorial service there"},{"time":1154000,"text":"a few days later."},{"time":1156000,"text":"These are Serphas lighting juniper branches."},{"time":1159000,"text":"They believe juniper smoke is holy."},{"time":1162000,"text":"And the climbers stood around on the high rocks"},{"time":1166000,"text":"and spoke of the climbers who were lost"},{"time":1169000,"text":"up near the summit,"},{"time":1171000,"text":"turning to the mountain, actually, to talk to them directly."},{"time":1176000,"text":"There were five climbers lost here."},{"time":1178000,"text":"This was Scott Fischer,"},{"time":1183000,"text":"Rob Hall,"},{"time":1185000,"text":"Andy Harris,"},{"time":1187000,"text":"Doug Hansen"},{"time":1189000,"text":"and Yasuko Namba."},{"time":1191000,"text":"And one more climber"},{"time":1193000,"text":"should have died that day, but didn't,"},{"time":1196000,"text":"and that's Beck Weathers."},{"time":1199000,"text":"He was able to survive"},{"time":1201000,"text":"because he was able to generate that incredible willpower,"},{"time":1204000,"text":"he was able to use all the power of his mind"},{"time":1207000,"text":"to save himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1210000,"text":"These are Tibetan prayer flags."},{"time":1212000,"text":"These Sherpas believe that"},{"time":1214000,"text":"if you write prayers on these flags,"},{"time":1216000,"text":"the message will be carried up to the gods,"},{"time":1219000,"text":"and that year, Beck's message was answered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1223000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1225000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}